  "texts": [
    "For a more comprehensive overview, we refer to [62,69,84].Fine-tuning a pre-trained language model is a popular approach for sequential transfer learning in NLP [13, 24, 37, For sequence tagging, Yang et al. [87] investigate multitask learning in the general domain with cross-domain, cross-application and cross-lingual transfer.",
    "In particular, target tasks with few labelled data benefit from related tasks.",
    "Lee et al. [51] successfully transfer pre-trained parameters from a big dataset to a small dataset in the biological domain.",
    "Schulz et al. [73] evaluate multi-task learning for argumentation mining with multiple datasets in the general domain and show that performance improves when training data for the tasks is sparse.",
    "For coreference resolution, Brack et al. [12] successfully apply sequential transfer learning and use a large dataset from the general domain to improve models for a small dataset in the scientific domain.For sentence classification, Mou et al."
